Boil a #pot{} of salted water for the noodles.

Drain the @tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Toss with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{1/2%tsp}(double for 4p) and @pepper{to taste}.

Place a pan over high heat with a glug of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}. Shift frequently to ensure it doesn't burn. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Transfer the tofu to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Reserve the pan to use later.

When the water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodles{150%g} and cook until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and toss to prevent sticking.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and halve the @Green Beans{75%g}.

Cut the @Cauliflower{1%unit} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Return the empty pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the cauliflower and cook until starting to char, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Next add the green beans.

Fry until slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the grated garlic and fry until fragrant, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pour the @Gochujang Paste{2%sachets}, @Soy Sauce{1%sachet} and @Ketjap Manis{1%sachet} into the pan along with @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml}(double both for 4p).

Stir well to combine and bring to the boil.

Cover and simmer until the veg is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}. Add a splash of @Water{to taste} to loosen the sauce if you feel it's too thick.

Toss the cooked noodles through the sauce until warmed through.

> Add the gochujang a little at a time, it's spicy!

Divide the spicy veg noodles between bowls.

Top with the crispy tofu.

Finish with a scattering of @Peanuts{20%g}.